  "metadata": {
    "title": "Dataset of 3D Garments with Sewing Patterns",
    "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.5267549",
    "publication_date": "2021-06-08",
    "description": "<p>The Dataset of 3D Garments with Sewing patterns contains more than 23500&nbsp;3D garment models with their corresponding sewing patterns, each representing unique garment design. The upload is organized by type for the 12 garment types of the train group, and the <a href=\"https://zenodo.org/api/files/82d24e49-a652-46d2-9d9f-7197ec4addc5/test.zip?versionId=caf48bdc-cf01-444d-a05f-74942a7483b5\">test.zip</a> contains garments of 9 types from the test group.&nbsp;<br>\n<br>\nThe detailed documentation of the dataset is provided in the accompanying&nbsp;<a href=\"https://zenodo.org/api/files/82d24e49-a652-46d2-9d9f-7197ec4addc5/Datasheet%20for%20Dataset%20of%203D%20Garments%20with%20Sewing%20Patterns%20v1..pdf?versionId=c27d0083-335f-4c0f-9c15-cc84361c1677\">Datasheet</a>.<br>\n<br>\nGarment samples are obtained using the Garment Pattern Generator (available on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/maria-korosteleva/Garment-Pattern-Generator\">GitHub</a>) as presented in the paper&nbsp;<a href=\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Pq8FBz0gZHY\">Generating Datasets of 3D Garments with Sewing Patterns&nbsp;</a>(<em><strong>NeurIPS 2021 Track on Datasets and Benchmarks</strong></em>)</p>",
    "access_right": "open",
